Meta: description-:
Our Titan Glute ham is one of the smoothest adjusting glute ham developing machines on the market, by using linear ball bearings and guide rods the unit adjusts using one hand with ease.

Since the adjustment takes less than 3 seconds as it uses a pull pin not a tightening knob it allows athletes of different heights to train on the same unit in a group and not waste 30-45 seconds adjusting the machine.

Features 

Independent Durable knee pads with anti-bacterial upholstery 12" wide by 8" thick for comfort

Over sized step up platforms with Diamond plate grip for easy loading and unloading

Foot hold is adjustable front to back with 7 adjustment points and up and down with 2 adjustment points

Foot hold uses a two roller construction allow athletes to easily get in and out of the machine without the ability to catch their ankle on the bottom pad
Meta: features-2: Linear Ball Bearings for smooth one hand adjustment

Meta: description-:
The Posterior Chain combo unit combines two of the most important lower body development machines in any gym, the Reverse Hyper machine and the Glute Ham Developer. 

With the ability to quickly adjust due to our stainless steel construction system using guide rods and a pull pin athletes can adjust the machine to be different depths in less than 3 seconds.

Features 

9 Adjustment points

Two weight pegs

Logo Spot

Pad and rollers are covered with
anti-bacterial upholstery

8" Single roller design allow the user
to get in and out of the machine
quickly

Athletes over 6' 4"need added stilts to properly do reverse hyper movements

Meta: description-:
The Renegade Bench was designed to be both a more compact and cost effective bench. Due to its smaller frame and lighter weight it is easier to wheel around compared to our Titan bench making it an ideal dumbbell/utility bench.

With pad dimensions of 11"x 34" the Renegade bench is slightly smaller than the Titan Bench which has a 11"x 41" pad. 

The Renegade Bench does not stand up on its end like the Titan bench does for storage
Meta: warranty_111:
Because we cut no corners in our design and manufacturing process we stand behind all Stray Dog Strength products with our industry leading warranty.

-Lifetime warranty on all welds and frames

-1 Year warranty on all moving parts

-60 Day warranty on all upholstery and pads

Meta: description-:
Our Decline/Flat Bench is a great piece of equipment with an extra wide pad at 19" that tappers to 9" athletes can feel more comfortable as more of their back is supported by the pad.

Features

6 adjustable angles from -25 to 0

Vertical storage when not in use

Foam rollers covered in marine grade upholstery to keep feet locked into position
Meta: features-3: Rollers also work for split squats ect.

Name: Hex Bar Storage
Short description: We designed our Hex Bar storage with a bolt together design for cheaper shipping and open ends allowing the end of the bar to hover over the ground and not get banged up in a bar sleeve. \n \nThe holes have 4.5″ between them making them 7″ apart on center which allows for 6 hex bars to be stored without having to skip any holes. Does not accommodate monster hex bars with handles over 4.5″ high.
Description:
DIMENSIONS

  • Length: 46"
  • Width: 17"
  • Height: 9.5"

Key Features

  • Holds 6 Hexbars with raised handles
  • Built with 1/4” thick USA steel
  • Black textured powder coat
  • Laser cut Stray Dog logo
  • Free standing design
  • Mounting holes to give option to mount to floor
  • Product Sell Sheet
Purchase note: Stray Dog products are made to order with a lead time of 6-4 weeks.
Tags: 6 bar storage, bar storage, hex bar storage, specialty bar storage

The Stray Dog Strength Dip Attachment was designed to be the best dip attachment on the market. With the ability to attach to 1" or  5/8" holes this attachment will work on virtually any brand rack out there.

Our utility roller was designed to do much more than just keep your knees locked in for Lat pull downs. Due to it's smooth rotation you can do various exercise such as split squats, feet elevated push ups, Nordic curls, and more exercises.

The wooden rod not only allows the roller to rotate more smoothly it also keeps the integrity of the pad so even heavy loads of split squats over time will not break down the foam.

The inside of the utility roller frame has 3 screwed in plastic pieces  one for each rack contact point to protect the rack post.

The larger lever and SPRING LOADED SNAP LATCH ensures easy installation and removal of the collar during workouts. The exceptional clamping force keeps the weights secured during workouts, while the elastomer pads and the resin frame protects the bar and plates from damage. LOCK-JAW PRO 2 is your ideal choice for serious lifters, high-impact workouts, and anytime bumper plates are used on a bar.

Dimensions

3.5”H x 3.75” W x 2”D
Meta: features-3: Large clip for single hand adjustment
Meta: warranty_111:
Click here for full Warranty Information found on LockJaw Collars website 

Within ten (10) days after discovery of the issue, Customer must provide proof of purchase, description
of complaint, the product(s) in question, name, address, phone, and email if available. AVUS DESIGN LP or agent
will only replace or issue credit after receipt of said item(s). This Warranty does not apply to unreasonable use
or damage. All Warranty claims are subject to return and inspection for credit. Products that have worn out due
to excessive use are not covered under the Warranty. Pad and/or part replacement service may be available
upon request for some products. Documentation of original purchase date, including customer name and
address must be submitted with Warranty claim

Name: Half Rack Spotter Arm
Short description: Our Half Rack spotter arms were not designed just as a safety spotter arm for when athletes fail a lift, they have 11 holes per arm for attachments. \n \n*Spotter arms are sold individually* and only fit racks with inline 1" holes, not offset holes.
Description:
Key Features:
  • Heavy-duty construction made from 3x3 11 gauge tubing and 1/4" steel plate
  • Top plastic protection for bar
  • Inside plastic protection for rack
  • All plastic secured with countersunk screws with thread lock to prevent plastic from coming off
  • Pin has a 20-degree tapper to allow for quick adjustments on the rack
  • Compatible with 3″x3″ racks with 1″ holes 2" on center
  • Includes standard hitch pin to lock spotter arm to rack
HALF SPOTTER ARMS ARE SOLD INDIVIDUALLY
Tags: spotter arms
Attribute 1 value(s): Gold, Yellow, Orange, Red, Navy, Green, Royal Blue, Silver, White, Black Texture, Clear Coat

Meta: description-:
By putting holes down the length of the spotter arm it allows the spotter arm to be modular with the ability to attach our attachments to it.

We discontinued our seat dedicated attachment as it is more cost effective to add the seat to the spotter arm.

With the ability to put our utility loops in the spotter arm it opens up all kinds of possibilities for body weight training.  Athletes can several exercises including, inverted rows, pull ups, incline push ups at whatever height they want as the spotter arm adjusts to 37 holes on the rack post.

Name: UHMW Bar Cups
Short description: Our UMHW Bar Cups are designed to protect the knurling on the barbell as well as the paint on the rack post due to the plastic pieces are on all wear points of the rack post for protection.\n\nBar cups can be made in 4-8 weeks as they are a smaller item
Description:
Key Features:
  • 1.5" thick solid UHMW insert to protect the bar in all directions
  • The pin has a 20-degree tapper to allow for quick adjustments on the rack
  • Inside plastic protection for rack
  • All plastic secured with countersunk screws with thread lock to prevent plastic from coming off
  • Heavy-duty construction made out of 1" round and 1/4" sheet steel
  • Compatible with 3″x3″ racks with 1″ holes 2″ on center
  • Sold as a left and right pair

Meta: description-:
Our UMHW Bar cups were designed to extend the life of the bar by  using UMHW plastic and designed to not scratch up the rack post as the inside has 2 plastic pieces.

Our Tapered pin allows athletes to quickly adjust the bar cup even using one hand as the pin fits in the hole smoother and there is not a pin to pull to adjust they just twist in and out.

Because we cut no corners in our design and manufacturing process we stand behind all Stray Dog Strength products with our industry leading warranty.

-Lifetime warranty on all welds and frames

-1 Year warranty on all moving parts

Meta: description-:
Our Bolt on bar storage was designed to extend the life of the barbell by having an open construction the end of the bar will rest on the rubber floor instead of the end of a steel tube which over time will damage the bar sleeve.

With traditional bar storages "bar pillows" are being manufactured to add to them to extend the life of the bar, with our bar storage you don't need a bar pillow as the rubber gym floor is the pillow.

Meta: description-:
Our CNC Stitched wear covers are a great touch to a facility or home gym as they make the benches look much more custom as they are not just displaying the facilities colors but also logos.

These can be added to non Stray Dog Strength benches as long as the pad can be removed from the frame to attach the wear cover.

CNC stitching allows you to choose more detailed logos also makes them all the same, with a $40 set up fee and then $70 per wear cover these can be replaced 10 years down the line for only $70 as we will keep artwork on file.

Extends the life of your pad by adding an extra layer of upholstery

Wear covers can be fully customized have your schools, name, logos, or anything else that can be stitched

Short description:
• Printed on 3M vinyl with protective coating so colors will not fade over time
  • CNC cut to the shape of your logo

    • CNC cut to the shape of your logo

Name: Titan Adjustable Bench

Raised Feet for Stability

Lateral Stability Supports

Ladder Adjustments

Logo Option

Meta: description-:
Our Titan Bench is a very sturdy adjustable bench allowing athletes to choose the adjustment that is right for them and also saves space by storing standing up out of the way.

Features  

Five adjustable back pad positions from 0 to 85 degrees

Three adjustable seat positions form 0 to 25 degrees

Pad locking mechanism to allow bench to be safety stored vertically when not in use

Sturdy wheels for easy movement

Integrated spotter platform for when bench is in the inclined position

Extremely durable pad utilizing military grade nylon webbing around the perimeter
that is double stitched to marine grade upholstery

Meta: description-:
The Stray Dog Strength power bar was designed as an all purpose bar to meet your training needs, with a 190,000 PSI Tensile strength rating this bar will stay solid for years to come.

Features

  • American made using USA steel
  • 28.5 MM Shaft Diameter
  • Length 87"
  • Black Cerakote shaft
  • 190,000 PSI Rating
  • Zinc coated Silver Sleeves
  • Bronze Bushing
  • Moderate Knurling
Meta: warranty_111:
Warranty Per Manufacture Solid Bar Fitness

Limited Lifetime Warranty against manufacturer defects. Does not cover damage due to negligent or faulty use, handling, maintenance, alteration or storage by the user. Bar damage and bending is usually always due to dropping on a rack or bench (the bar hits before the plates) and is not covered by this warranty, but we will replace the shaft for $100. All warranty claims handled on a case by case basis.

Name: Mid Row
Short description: Our Mid Row machine was developed to allow athletes to bilaterally row and not cheat with the weak side of their body by overcompensating with the dominant side.\n\n
Description:
Key Features

  • Knurled handles that move in three planes of motion
  • Arms move independently
  • Adjustable chest and seat pad with anti-bacterial upholstery
  • Seat is removable allowing you to row from an athletic stance
  • Foot pegs to help lock into position
  • Band pegs for increased resistance
  • Custom logo options
  • Floor mounting tabs

Meta: description-:
The Mid Row Machine was designed with the athlete in mind, the knurled handles are easier to grip and also rotate in 3 planes of motion allowing the athlete to rotate their wrists when pulling to the position most comfortable for them.

With 6 chest pad and 12 seat pad adjustment points as well as a removable seat for athletic stance rows, athletes can find the position most comfortable for them to row.

The plastic protector on the arms will keep them from getting scratched by the handles overtime. 

There is also a band attachment point for added resistance, a foot peg to lock the athlete in and a logo spot for a personalized touch.
Meta: features-1-: Independently moving Knurled Handles with Plastic protection piece
Meta: features-3: Remove seat for Athletic Stance Rows

Name: Landmine
Short description: We have two landmine options, Fixed and Adjustable which both are comprised of the same parts but the Fixed unit comes with a lock washer and nut while the Adjustable comes with our Adjustable Nut. \n \nThe adjustable landmine is very versatile, with the ability for it to go into any hole on a Rack you can hit different angles that were not possible with a traditional bolt on landmine
Description:
Key Features

  • Works with an bar with 2” OD end
  • Universal joint with 360 degrees of motion
  • Move up and down rack post to achieve the best angle
Purchase note: Stray Dog products are made to order with a lead time of 6-4 weeks.
Tags: abs, adjustable landmine, Attachment, core, Landmine, movable landmine, Press, squat

Meta: description-:
Our Movable landmine is a very versatile attachment, with the ability for it to go into any hole on a Rack you can hit different angles that were not possible with a traditional bolt on landmine.

Rest the bar on the spotter arm when loading, between movements and to get set up so you don't waste any motion doing overhead press, squats or any other movement with the landmine set high on the post.

The Adjustable Nut has plastic to protect the rack post which is attached with two screws and no adhesive to last longer.

Name: Alpha Half Rack
Short description: The Alpha Rack was designed to bring our modular rack system and unique attachments to the 1" hole ecosystem making our products compatible with other brands. 3x3" 11 gauge tubing all over with 1" holes spaced 2" apart on center. \n \nComes with proprietary guide rod hole pattern crossmembers to add in cable machine attachments.
Description:
Stray Dog Alpha Racks feature a modular design that allows you to customize your rack exactly to your needs. Alpha racks are constructed entirely out of 3x3 11 gauge USA steel tubing with 1" holes every 2" apart. The front upright posts have laser-cut numbers to quickly identify hole positions for attachments. Previous Next

Meta: description-:
Our Alpha Rack Series was redesigned from our old Titan, Renegade and Genesis series to have 1" holes and 3x3 tubing opposed to the 3/4" holes and 3x3 tubing we used in the past.

Alpha Racks crossmembers include our proprietary guide rod hole pattern to add a machine attachments such as a Lat pulldown, Cable column or a belt squat/Lat pull down combo.

With the ability to add a machine attachment after you purchase the rack your equipment can evolve with your facility as your training needs and budget changes.

Each side of an Alpha Half rack can have a machine attachment giving customers he ability to add a machine to their room without compromising floor space.

Frame Package: 4 Uprights (2 numbered), 4 30" Crossmembers, 1 Straight Chin up bar and Stray Dog Strength Laser cut name plate.

ST Package:  4 Uprights (2 numbered), 4 30" Crossmembers, 1 Straight Chin up bar, 1 Pair of Basic Bar Cups, 1 Change plate storage, 4 Fixed weight pegs and a Stray Dog Strength Laser cut name plate.

STR Package: 4 Uprights (2 numbered), 4 30" Crossmembers, 1 Straight Chin up bar, 1 Pair of UMHW Bar Cups, 1 Pair of spotter arms, 2 Change plate storage, 4 Fixed weight pegs and a Stray Dog Strength Laser cut name plate.

MG Package: 4 Uprights (2 numbered), 4 30" Crossmembers, 1 Multi-Grip Chin up bar, 1 Pair of UMHW Bar Cups, 1 Pair of spotter arms, 2 Change plate storage, 4 weight pegs and a Stray Dog Strength Laser cut name plate.

Stray Dog Triad Racks feature a modular design that allows you to customize your rack exactly to your needs. Triad racks are constructed entirely out of 3x3 11 gauge USA steel tubing with 1" holes every 2" apart. The front upright posts have laser-cut tick marks on every hole to quickly identify hole positions for attachments. Previous Next

  • One pair of basic metal bar cups
  • One change plate storage
  • Four 14" weight storage pegs

Meta: description-:
The Triad Half rack is a patent pending design by Stray Dog Strength, using 3 uprights instead of 4 compared to a normal half rack.

The Triangle construction allows for a more sturdy frame, a smaller footprint and more cost effective solution as it uses less steel.

All Triad Racks come with built in bolt down tabs and concrete anchors as we recommend the unit be anchored to the floor if the front feet are not attached.

Package Options

Frame Package: Comes with 3 Posts, 2 Triangle Connectors, 1 Stray Dog Strength laser cut logo and a Straight pull up bar

ST Package: Comes with 3 posts, 2 Triangle Connectors, 1 Stray Dog Strength laser cut logo, Basic Bar Cups, Straight pull up bar, One change plate storage and 4 weight pegs

STR Package: Comes with 3 posts, 2 Triangle Connectors, 1 Stray Dog Strength laser cut logo, 4 weight pegs, 1 change plate storage, Straight pull up bar, UMHW Bar Cups, Spotter arms and hanging bar storage

MG Package: Comes with 3 posts, 2 Triangle Connectors, 1 Stray Dog Strength laser cut logo, 4 weight pegs, 1 change plate storage, Multi-Grip pull up bar, UMHW Bar Cups, Spotter arms and hanging bar storage

Name: Triad Double Half Rack

Name: ATR Lat Pull Down
Short description: The ATR Lat Pull Down uses a 1:1 ratio on a 250 pound weight stack allowing athletes to feel the full weight of the stack. The Fixed Low Pulley can be added on with 2 1" bolts. All ATR units are made out of 3×3 tubing with 1″ holes and 2″ hole spacing. Click here for an article further explaining ATR units  Click here for assembly instructions
Description:
Basic Package

Features:
  • Frame constructed with 8' rack uprights and 30" crossmembers
  • 250 lb weight stack with commercial-grade composite weight plates
  • Chrome-plated guide rods
  • Heavy-duty 1/4" steel coated cable

Deluxe Package

Features:
  • Frame constructed with 8' rack uprights and 30" crossmembers
  • 250 lb weight stack with commercial-grade composite weight plates
  • Chrome-plated guide rods
  • Heavy-duty 1/4" steel coated cable
  • One dual utility roller to lock in your knees
  • One Lat seat with half-rack spotter arm
  • One knurled lat bar
  • One dual storage hook to store cable attachments
Stray Dog Strength's Auxiliary Training Rack (ATR) was created in 2017 to combat the inefficiency of single-use machines commonly seen in weight rooms.  Traditional machines take up valuable floor space and limit athletes' to a single exercises. Our ATR takes a systematic approach to auxiliary work, which provides athletes with a functional station that increases efficiency for the athletes and the facility. If you are looking to maximize your team's training our ATR has the flexibility to meet your facility's needs. Key ATR Features:
  • Overflow lifting stations
  • Machines: Lat Pull Down, Low Row, Belt Squat, Adjustable Cable Column
  • Compatible with all Stray Dog rack attachments
  • Small footprint
  • Storage solutions for medballs, slam balls, dumbbells, kettlebells, foam rollers, bands and more
**ATR's are designed to be anchored to the ground and attached to at least one other ATR or rack**

Because the trolley goes directly on the upright you can attach our utility roller attachment to keep your knees locked down for Lat Pull downs.

Meta: description-:
The Belt squat attachment was designed to allow athletes who are injured or athletes who don't need the extra spine compression but still want to load the lower body for squats to gain strength.

Our Rack attached belt squat is not just for athletes with back issues, athletes with upper body issues that cannot hold a bar such as shoulder, arm, hand or even collar bone injuries can safely squat with the Stray Dog Strength Rack attached belt squat.

Deluxe Option comes with Spud INC Adjustable Belt Squat Belt and Dual Storage Hook

Our Belt Squat/Lat Pull Down combo unit is our only plate loaded machine attachment as many athletes squat more than 250 pounds.  With two 16" weight pegs athletes can train with virtually any load they choose without compressing their spine and stress on the upper body.

The adjustable stop is necessary when using the belt squat as different height athletes will want to start and stop the weight at different heights to avoid awkward half reps. The adjustable stop should be removed while doing Lat pull downs as the trolley starts at the bottom and the stop is not needed.

Meta: description-:
Our Plain side ATR is basically one side of a rack half rack as it is comprised of two 96" ticked rack posts and two 30" crossmembers.

Plain side ATR's are common to be connected by our 43" or 72" storage trays or beam connectors for attachments. Often they are connected to an ATR cable column, Lat pull down or belt squat to create a lifting station.

To create a "power rack" without weight pegs you can purchase two ATR plain sides and connect them with a pullup bar or any other connector that is 43" to create a lifting station when you add bar cups.

You can also create a "cube" which is basically an ATR not up against the wall that makes two lifting stations like a double sided half rack but without the extra post for shared plate storage.

ATR Plain sides come with our 30" crossmember with the hole pattern to add on a machine allowing your equipment to be adaptable to your current training needs and budget.

The top beam connector was designed to link racks or ATR units together adding more stability to them while also adding a high beam for attachments such as utility loops, Multi Grip chin up,  Logo topper and more.

Meta: description-:
The fixed low pulley foot pegs store out of the way when not in use with two pull pins, giving you the ability to lock your feet in when doing low rows but not get in the way when not using the unit.

The fixed pulley can be added to our ATR Lat Pull down or Rack Attached Lat Pull down to add the ability to do low row movements while keeping the feet locked in.

Name: Change Plate Storage
Short description: The Change Plate storage allows you to store 2.5, 5 and 10 LBS change plates with ease without taking up as much room on the rack post as 3 separate pegs would. Only one bolt is needed to attach the unit as the fingers in the back are spaced 3″ to grip the outsides of the post and keep it from rotating and also double as storage fingers.\n\n1″ option comes with one 1″ bolt, one 1″ washer, one 1″ lock washer and one 1″ nut. The 5/8″ option comes with one 5/8″ bolt, one 5/8″ washer, one 5/8″ lock washer and one 5/8″ nut.

  • Fits on 3"x3" tubing with 1" holes

Meta: description-:
The Unit has one 1" hole and two 5/8" holes which are spaced 4" apart, the storage fingers on the back also keep the change plate storage from rotating.

The Change Plate Storage has been a popular storage solution for our customers as it allows them to store all 3 kinds of change plates as well as clips, bands and other miscellaneous items.

This is the second version, the original had 1 peg up top for 2.5's and 2 pegs below for 5's and 10's we found that some brand plates cannot fit both 5 and 10 LBS plates next to each other so we flipped it upside down and now recommend to put the 10 LBS plates on bottom and the 2.5's and 5's on top.

Features 2 storage fingers on the back which are angled up at 3 degrees for more secure storage of clips, bands, chains, straps or any other item under 50 LBS.

The change plates storage allows you to store more weights without taking up as much space on the post, with two of the 3 pegs being off to the side of the rack post it leaves more holes above it open compared to using 3 separate pegs to store change plates.

One Change plate comes with the ST Alpha Half rack but the STR and MG Package have 2 change plate storages per rack.

One change plate comes with the ST, STR and MG Triad Rack package.

Meta: description-:
The rack attached Lat Pull down from Stray Dog Strength has a 1:1 cable ratio allowing you to feel the true weight of the 250 pound sectorized weight stack.

Basic Package comes with 2 guide rods, 2 carabiners, 1 chain,250 LBS weight stack ,1 pulley housing (accent color) with pulleys and cable.

Deluxe Package includes, 2 guide rods,2 carabiners, 1 chain, 250 LBS weight stack, 1 Lat bar, 1 Dual storage hook, 1 Lat seat attachment, 1 utility roller and 1 pulley housing with pulleys and cable.

Our fixed low pulley with movable foot pegs can also be added to add a low row station to the unit.

We include a chain so different height athletes can comfortably use the high pulley, which allows shorter athletes to just reach up to grab the Lat bar and not have to stand on the seat to reach it.

Pulley top is the Accent color option, the trolley is always black

The Rack attached cable column is a great way to pack as much functionality into the footprint of the rack as possible. The trolley can be adjusted to any hole on the upright allowing athletes to hit virtually any cable exercise possible.

The Trolley goes right onto the rack post which allows you to use the cable column post for other attachments or as a lifting station when not in use.

The Trolley pivots side to side allowing the athlete to choose the location they want to do the movement as they can use the pulley straight on or to either side allowing multiple athletes to train on the same rack and work around each other safely.

*This attachment is only compatible with Stray Dog Strength Alpha Racks*

Meta: description-:
Deluxe version comes with Spud INC Belt Squat Belt and storage hook for Lat bar, belt and low pulley cable.

The Belt squat attachment was designed to allow athletes who are injured or athletes who don't need the extra spine compression but still want to load the lower body for squats to gain strength.

Our Rack attached belt squat is not just for athletes with back issues, athletes with upper body issues that cannot hold a bar such as shoulder, arm, hand or even collar bone injuries can safely squat with the Stray Dog Strength Rack attached belt squat.

Comes with Spud INC Adjustable Belt Squat Belt

Our Belt Squat/Lat Pull Down combo unit is our only plate loaded machine attachment as many athletes squat more than 250 pounds.  With two 16" weight pegs athletes can train with virtually any load they choose without compressing their spine and stress on the upper body.

The adjustable stop is necessary when using the belt squat as different height athletes will want to start and stop the weight at different heights to avoid awkward half reps. The adjustable stop should be removed while doing Lat pull downs as the trolley starts at the bottom and the stop is not needed.
Meta: features-3: Adjustable Stop for different height athletes
Meta: features-4: Weight pegs store up with a pin
Meta: movements-3: Lat pull down top of rep
Meta: movements-4: Lat pull down bottom of rep

Utility Loop
Short description: The Utility Loop is a versatile attachment that allows you to do body weight exercises and doubles as storage for balls, ropes or whatever else you need it for. Does not fit Metric or Imported "1 Inch" Holes.\n\n*Utility Loops are sold individually*
Description:
Utility Loops are designed to be the most versatile attachment in your training arsenal, as they attach to any of the 1" holes on our rack/ATR posts and can hold the heaviest of athletes body weight up for dips, body weight rows, pull ups, or any exercise performed on parallette bars.

The utility loop is more of a rounded rectangle than a true loop which gives it the option to be used in a neutral grip, supinated grip or pronated grip.

They also are great for holding a Pilates ball, slam ball or medicine ball.
Categories: Attachments, Featured Products, Rack System > Rack Attachments, Rack System > Rack Storage, Storage
Tags: ball storage, band anchor, body weight, dips, pull blocks, pull ups, rows
Meta: description-:
Our utility loop was designed to be a true utility attachment with the ability to go into any rack hole and secure with a detent pin the storage and movement possibilities are endless.

Our Utility Loops also fit in our spotter arms allowing you to use them as technique blocks, or body weight piece for dips, rows, push ups, pull ups and more exercises.

The utility loop is a cost effective way to add a neutral grip to your rack system allowing you to do pull ups, rows, dips and many more exercises in the hand position that is most comfortable for the athlete as they can also do supinated or pronated grips as well as neutral.

Name: Movable Storage Hook
Short description: Our Storage Hooks were designed to fix an issue in every weight room, getting items off the ground to create better flow in rooms allowing for more time spent training. The hooks are rated to hold up to 80 LBS and can hold anything from Barbells, Hex Bars, Dumbbells, Cable Attachments and more. Click here for a video  The 1" and 5/8" hooks will be back in stock in early to mid March. Hooks are sold individually and are designed for 1" holes with 2" hole spacing or a single 5/8" hole depending on option.
Description: Our Storage Hooks were designed to fix an issue in every weight room, getting items off the ground to create better flow in rooms allowing for more time spent training and less time spent moving equipment. These hooks can hold anything up to 80 pounds, easily hold a hex bar using one hook or hang a regular bar with two hooks across the back of your rack post.\n\n
Tags: attachment holder, band holder, bar holder, hook, movable hook, storage
Meta: description-:
The Storage Hooks were designed to attach to two 1" holes, if you only have one hole open you can attach the storage hook but it will not be as sturdy as only one of the attachment slits is locked in.

The Storage hook is wide enough to store a barbell or hex bar allowing you to store virtually any small item in the gym from, straps and bands to attachments and barbells.

Our Storage hooks are rated for 80 LBS per storage hook.
Meta: features-5: Small but wide enough to hold bars and most attachments

Name: Marrs Bar
Short description: The Marrs-Bar Safety Squat Bar was designed to greatly reduce discomfort and imbalance when performing barbell back squats, front squat and lunges. If you’re shopping for the best safety squat bar, look no further the Marrs bar is the answer.
Categories: Bars and weights, Discount Exempt, Bars and weights > Bars > Specialty Bars
Tags: bars, marrs bar, saftey squat bar, squat bar
Meta: description-:
Thanks to the built-in padded harness, the Marrs-Bar safety squat bar distributes the payload throughout a much greater area of the upper body eliminating pinch points and discomfort in the neck and shoulders common with traditional squat bars and power bars.

This added stability makes it possible to do hands free squats and takes away the awkwardness, discomfort and imbalance when front squatting for the most comfortable and productive front squats you’ve ever experienced.

Because the payload sits closer to the hip hinge when performing back squats, you will immediately notice the ability to move more weight.

The front handles on the Marrs-bar safety squat bar are positioned to reduce and even eliminate shoulder joint stress during barbell squats which makes squatting possible again for those with reduced range of motion and/or pain in the shoulders.

The Marrs-Bar is an excellent rehabilitation tool and promotes proper form for reduced risk of injury. Each bar is compatible with Olympic plates and bumper plates with 2” center hole

Specs 

  • Weight: 65 lbs.
  • Fully welded.
  • Dimensions: 89" L x 24" W (with handles)
  • Bar Diameter: 1.5" diameter solid steel bar and harness.
  • Sleeve Diameter: 2" diameter for Olympic plates and bumpers.
  • Sleeve Construction: Fully welded and machined.
  • Bar and Harness Coating: Zinc.
  • Sleeve Coating: Black oxide.
Meta: movements-5: Front Squat Bar position from behind

Name: Logo Topper
Short description: Our Logo Topper comes in both a laser cut option or a decal option.
Description: \n\n
Tags: custom logo, decal, laser cut, logo
Meta: description-:
Our Laser cut logo topper can be attached behind the pull up bar in an MG rack putting it inside the rack or can be attached between racks on the beam connector putting the logo outside the rack. 

The Laser Cut Logo Topper has two spots for our Octagon metal overlay cut outs for logos and one spot in the middle for words.

Or instead of 2 Octagon logs and 1 text laser cut out you can get a full sticker that covers the entire piece of metal (example is Heath logo of Bulldog log with Josh Lohrman below it).

Sticker logos can be higher in detail as they are CNC printed and not cut out of steel.

Laser cut hexagon logo cut out is 6.5" x 6.5" 

Laser Cut word cut out is 25.5" x 4.5"

Name: Stray Dog Logo Hitch Pin
Short description: Our Stray Dog Logo Hitch pin was designed to bring an extra element of branding and detail to our products, most companies use standard black, silver or red pins we decided to go with a black pin to match all color schemes and also add our Stray Dog Logo.\n\n
Description: Our new products now come with our custom Stray Dog Logo hitch pin which is a black pin with a black handle that includes our half dog head logo followed by "Stray Dog" in White.
Tags: attachment pin, custom hitch pin, DIY, hitch pin, parts
Meta: description-:
The Stray Dog Hitch pin was chosen after testing over 10 different hitch pin styles, we tested different lengths, handle options, dent pin options and even different material pins before deciding this was the best option and custom branding it.

Due to it's 5  Inch long pin athletes do not have to worry about the pin wiggling its way out of the hole while using the unit even if they forget to attach the detent pin. 

Comes with our Spotter arms, Lat seat, Step up attachment, Dual Utility Roller and Dip Attachment.

Name: Adjustable Nut
Short description: The Adjustable Nut goes on threaded 1" rods, they come with many of our products but can be added to any threaded 1" rod. They have UMHW plastic on the back that protects the post, when tightened down they create a very  sturdy yet easy to adjust solution.
Tags: adjustable nut, beltsquat, Landmine, lever arms, nut
Meta: description-:
The Adjustable nut was designed as a quick tighten solution to secure our attachments to the rack post. By using a threaded pin and adjustable nut you are able to easily adjust attachments to any hole on the post while the UHMW Plastic protects the post.

Comes with our Adjustable Landmine, Basic and Deluxe Lever Arms, Belt Squat Stop and Adjustable Weight Peg and Alpha Utility Roller
Meta: features-3: Plastic is screwed in no adhesive
Meta: features-4: Grooves designed to snugly fit fingers
Meta: features-5: Grooves designed to snugly fit fingers

Name: Logo Beam Connector
Short description: The Logo beam connector was designed to allow customers to customize their racks to show school, brand, company, or personal pride by adding custom logos to the inside of racks. \n \nComes with Stray Dog Logo name plate, the logo spot and word spot are both customization options that do not come standard.
Tags: custom, logo, school pride
Attribute 1 value(s): Gold, Yellow, Orange, Red, Navy, Green, Royal Blue, Silver, White, Black Texture, Gloss Black
Meta: description-:
Our logo beam connector was created for our Alpha rack series to go between the back two rack posts adding both a custom logo spot and also stability to the rack.

The logo beam crossmember has two logo spots and one word spot in the middle for laser cut outs. 

The logo beam connector can have laser cut outs on both sides allowing double half racks to show logos on both sides. One of the sides is flush and the other side has a 3x3 piece of tubing to attach a pull up bar or attachments.

Name: Functional Trainer
Short description: The ATR functional trainer was created using two ATR cable columns connected by our 43" or 72" crossmember which can have our multi grip chin up bar added to it to create a chin up station. \n \nWhen connected at 43" the Functional Trainer is basically a half rack and can be lifted off of by adding bar cups and or spotter arms and sliding the trolley out of the way to the top of the post.
Tags: cable, cable crossover, cable stack, cables, Functional Trainer, machine
Meta: description-:
The ATR Functional Trainer is made up out of existing ATR parts, by using our rack uprights with 1" holes you can use the post for other attachments if you move the cable trolley to the top of the post. 

The ATR Functional Trainer comes Standard with two basic ATR cable columns connected by either a 72" or 43" crossmember.

 You can add storage trays such as dumbbell, kettlebell or ball trays to either the 43" or 72" functional trainer. You also can add an MG pull up bar or utility loops to the crossmember to add a pull up station. 

ATR Functional trainers that are connected at 43" can be used as a lifting station if you add bar cups and or spotter arms making them one of the most versatile racks out there.

The Step Up Plate has 5 holes, the outside and the center holes are 1" and the two holes adjacent to the center hole are 5/8". If you are using it as a Step Up you only need one pin but when using as a ball target two pins are required to secure the plate.
Categories: Attachments, Featured Products, Rack System > Rack Attachments
Tags: ball target, box jump, movable plate, step up, wall ball
Meta: description-:
Mount The Step Up Plate to the spotter arm for adjustable height step ups, box squats, sandbag or stone platform or attach it to the upright for a target or back support.

The Step Up Plate comes with one Hitch Pin to use for step ups and other exercises, but if you want to use it as a ball target two pins would be required to keep it pinned to the post/protect the post.

The Step Up plate allows athletes and coaches to have a versatile variable height platform that can be used for step ups, box jumps, box squats, ball target and other exercises.

The Step Up Plate attaches to the spotter arm with one hitch pin or to the rack post with two hitch pins as if you only use one hitch pin it will move and hit the rack post on the side without a pin
The Step Up plate is a unique piece of equipment to Stray Dog strength, we can’t wait to see all the ways our customers find to use the Step Up Plate!

Short description: The Removable Chalk Bowl was designed to attach to 1" holes and 3x3" 11 gauge tubing, (does not fit metric racks) this attachment does not attach with a hitch pin or adjustable nut but instead has slits that lock into the rack holes with gravity. You also can put a bolt in to keep it from being removable. *Not compatible with Import/Metric racks* Each Chalk bowl comes with a 2 OZ block of Stray Dog Lifting Chalk
Tags: bowl, chalk, chalk bowl, chalk storage, clean gym, dog bowl
Meta: description-:
Most people spend lots of time keeping their gym clean so why make more of a mess than you need to? This is why we designed our chalk bowl with a lid to keep one of the most messy items in any gym, chalk contained where you need it.

Our chalk bowl also takes up a very small space compared to traditional chalk bowls which often are large units with wheels as ours attaches to a rack post and only sticks out 14" from the post.

As chalk is not used in every workout the chalk bowl also doubles as an adjustable stand to store phones, drinks and or programing sheets.

Meta: description-:
Finding the right jump rope can be tricky, athletes of different sizes need different length jump ropes to properly jump rope which is why we chose this adjustable jump rope as our Stray Dog Speed Jump Rope.

The bearing in the top of the handle makes the jump rope effortlessly spin to allow athletes to focus on jumping and rhythm and not spinning the jump rope.

Name: Rack/ATR Height Modification
Short description: Custom rack height add on, this will cover any machine attachment that needs cut down that was also ordered at the same time as the rack. The guide rods and the cable will be modified to the appropriate height as well.\n\nPlease indicate in the notes when placing an order how high you want the highest part on the rack/ATR to be, if you your ceiling is 94" don't have us cut it to 94" because it will not fit go 2" shorter than the ceiling height so in this example 92" for a 94" ceiling to get the maximum functionality.
Tags: custom height, height mod, height modification
Meta: description-:
The shortest we have ever cut a rack down to was 80" from 96".

By cutting down the rack you limit the cable travel for cable machines, so if you are getting a Lat pull down especially you should cut down the unit as little as possible to maximize functionality.

A good rule of thumb is to go 2" or 4" shorter than ceiling height as we can only cut down in 2" increments.
Meta: features-2: We aim to be 2-4" below the ceiling height
Meta: features-3: Yes we can modify cable attachments too

Custom Crossmember Brackets
Short description: The Custom Crossmember Brackets were designed to allow customers to make a crossmember at a custom length. The slotted bracket allows customers to create a custom length crossmember to connect different brand 1" hole 3x3" racks or our ATR units to other brand racks. By combining the brackets and our 3x3" tubes you can create a custom length crossmember available in 2" increments The Universal and Crossmember Brackets are .25" thick each, the tube that goes between them will have to be .5" shorter than the length you want as the bracket will fill in the missing .5". The Beam Connector Bracket is 3/8".
Categories: Featured Products, Rack System > Rack Parts, Stray Dog Auxiliary
Tags: compatible, crossmember, custom, DIY, slotted bracket
Attribute 1 value(s): Regular Crossmember Bracket, Universal Crossmember Bracket, Beam Connector Bracket
Meta: description-:
3x3" Tubing racks with 1" holes have become the industry standard over the last 10 years, but what has not become standard is the where that first 1" hole starts. Different brands racks all have their first hole dimension at a different height which makes connecting two different brand racks very difficult as the holes do not line up.

We have created a slotted bracket that accounts for that difference in the first hole height and allows different brand 3x3" 1" hole racks to be connected without making any modification to the rack and only adding a few bolts.

Our Beam Connector Bracket, which we have always sold with our Top Beam Connector will also allow different brand racks to be connected on top the crossmember opposed to bolted in like a crossmember.
Meta: features-1-: Connect different Brand 3x3 Uprights with 1" holes

Meta: description-:
Alpha Bench big pad 40" long x 12" wide x 2.25" Thick

Alpha Bench seat pad 12.5" long x 12" wide x 2.25" Thick

Total alpha bench frame is 58" x24.5" in the back and 8" wide in the front

The Alpha bench has 3 main features that make it stand out from the rest of the benches on the market. It is the only bench with the adjustment ladder on the back of the pad allowing for easier adjustment and a spotter plate to be where the ladder normally would be.

The Alpha bench has a lot of great features that make it stand out from other benches on the market, read our list below to better understand what makes the alpha bench special

The Premium pad has a steel back plate and comes with a non logo wear cover. The Standard pad is the same size as premium pad but without the steel back and wear cover.

1)Ladder Positions are cut into the back pad, not the frame. this allows for easier and quicker adjustments and is the only bench like this on the Market. All adjustment points are protected with plastic.

3) all adjustment points use bronze oil impregnated bushings allowing for smooth rotation and no metal on metal contact

4) 1.25" pad gap when in flat position

5) laser cut angle degree marking on back and seat pads

6) urethane stray dog logoed wheels with abec 7 bearings for easy Movement of bench

7) rubber bumpers that grip the floor and Doesn't allow the bench to slide

8) Vertical storage that keeps the pad off the ground

9) knurled handle that is a piece of our power bar (28.5 mM Black powder coat, American made steel)

10) Back pad support has holes for rack attachments when seat is inclined

11) TWO TONE PAINT OPTIONS FRAME AND ACCENT

two tone paint Options, frame and accent (red frame, silver accent shown)

12) laser Cut stray dog name plate which is accent color

13) FRAME IS CONSTRUCTED ENTIRELY OUT OF 3X3 11 GAUGE

frame is constructed entirely out of 3x3 11 Gauge tubing

14) Optional logo spot for decals or laser cut logos which can be customized

15) optional spotter plate. as the ladder is on the back of the seat not the frame it allows us to put the spotter plate where the ladder would be. this makes the footprint smaller.

16) bolt together design that will allow for ups Parcel shipping which will keep shipping costs down

GOAT Attachment
Short description: The GOAT Attachment was designed to be one of the most versatile attachments of all time, the bearings allow for smooth rotation and the brackets 5 adjustment holes allow you to pin in the tube at 11 different angles. The GOAT Attachment comes with the bracket, 24" tube with 1" and 2 hitch pins, attachments sold separately. The Tube cannot be swapped out for a smaller or longer tube and we will not sell just the bracket. Click here to watch a YouTube video on the GOAT Attachment.  \n \nThe 5/8" version is the same exact unit as the 1" but the pin is swapped out for a 5/8" pin and you will receive one 1" pin to pin the tube in at an angle and 1 5/8" pin to hold the unit on the upright. The pin goes behind the post not through it. So the holes on the tube are still 1" on the 5/8" version.
Categories: Attachments, Featured Products, Rack System > Machine Attachments, Rack System > Rack Attachments
Tags: bicep curls, curls, GOAT, hamstring curls, hip thrust, leg curl, leg extension, standing hamstring curls
Meta: description-:
The GOAT Attachment comes with the 24" Tube, Bracket with bearings, 2 Hitch Pins and 1 Rubber Bumper for the tube.

All attachments are sold separately, the tube is 3x3" with 1" holes so other brand rollers and weight pegs will be compatible.

To do a Leg Curl or Leg Extension either single or dual leg, you would need 2 roller pads and 1 Adjustable weight peg. Both our Single Utility Roller or Alpha Roller Pads would work.

To do Dorsiflexion/Plantarflexion step ups or pistol squats you would need to pair the Step Up Plate with the GOAT.

To do hip thrusts you would need 1 roller pad either Single Utility Roller or Alpha Roller and 1 Adjustable weight peg.

To do bicep curls you would need 1 Utility Loop, 1 roller pad either Single Utility Roller or Alpha Roller and 1 Adjustable weight peg.

The GOAT can also be connected to an ATR Cable Column or Cable Column Attachment to do weight stack resistance leg curls, leg extensions, weighted crunch, or back attack.

Multi Grip Cable/Landmine Attachment
Short description: The Multi Grip Cable/Landmine Attachment was designed to be a multi use attachment that can be used on cable machines or landmine units. We made a prototype of this bar back in 2020 that also had sleeves to load weights onto but opted to remove them as it made the bar heavy and awkward for cable or landmine movements. This version weighing in at 22 LBS this bar is sturdy but not too awkward/heavy for cable exercises.
